                                      ACCESS SPECIFIERS
                                  ===========================

-> These are used to specify  accessibility for our classes ,variables and methods.
-> In java, we have below 4  access specifiers.

    1.Public
    2.Private 
    3.Protected
    4.Default

Public: It is used to specify  global access for classes, variables, methods and Constructors.
Private: It is used to specify local access.Private variable,private methods,private constructors can't be accessed outside of the class.
Protected: Protected members can be accessed in same package and sub classes.
Default: Default members can be accessed in same package.





















